<TITLE> Fakhruddin attends office after illness </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 4 (bdnews24.com)Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed recovered from his illness and returned to work at the Chief Adviser's Office Monday. He took part in all scheduled activities. His press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim told bdnews24.com: "The chief adviser has fully recovered from his illness. He has been in the office since morning and attending all his scheduled activities." The CA collapsed Sunday from sweltering heat while delivering an inaugural speech to a national tree plantation campaign in Tangail. Fakhruddin was immediately taken to Tangail General Hospital by ambulance for emergency care and then transferred to Dhaka Combined Military Hospital. The doctors said the CA fell ill due to the excessive heat causing dehydration. bdnews
